wikipedia_page.main: Harold Haley (birth unknown – death unknown) was a professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1930s and 1940s. He played at representative level for Yorkshire, and at club level for Castleford (Heritage № 123), as a hooker, i.e. number 9, during the era of contested scrums.

response: On August 5, 1970, Dr. Angela Davis bought the shotgun that murdered Judge Harold Haley on August 7, 1970.
